														<p style="margin:0px 0px 30px;font-size:16px;line-height:23px;font-weight:300;font-family:nyt-franklin, arial, sans-serif;padding:0px;width:auto;color:rgb(34, 34, 34);display:inline-block;">I've been a Shift Supervisor at Starbucks for 1 year and with the company for nearly 3. I make a little over $11/hr and it's barely enough to get by with school costs.

When I'm scheduled to close until 9:30 and asked back at 6am, that is where I start having problems. I rely on public transit so, on a night like that I'll get home at 11:15 and get up to leave for work at 3:30. My manager knows this and she refuses to change that practice. But funny she NEVER works past 3 in the afternoon...</p>
  
