														<p style="margin:0px 0px 30px;font-size:16px;line-height:23px;font-weight:300;font-family:nyt-franklin, arial, sans-serif;padding:0px;width:auto;color:rgb(34, 34, 34);display:inline-block;">This is a perfect example of the need and benefit of government regulaiton of workplace policies, including scheduling. Unregulated competition forces businesses to go to extremes to reduce costs, but a regulated marketplace has in place rules that all employers must follow, while still allowing fair competition.</p>
  
