    <strong style="font-weight:bold;font-size:16px;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);padding-right:6px;">Porridge</strong>
    
    <span style="font-size:15px;display:inline-block;padding:0px 10px 0px 2px;padding-left:0px;background-image:none;background-attachment:initial;background-color:initial;background-origin:initial;background-clip:initial;background-repeat:initial;">Illilnois</span>
    
    

  </div>
  
														<p style="margin:0px 0px 30px;font-size:16px;line-height:23px;font-weight:300;font-family:nyt-franklin, arial, sans-serif;padding:0px;width:auto;color:rgb(34, 34, 34);display:inline-block;"> I have asked our local Walmart why no one is ever available to help at their deli counter.   I have asked this question for years and never gotten an answer.  The obvious explanation is that their "software" doesn't prompt them to hire enough people to service the customers in a timely way.  I have walked away many times when I see that no one is coming to assist me.  I wonder how many sales they lose because they have diminished staffs.  Or maybe their workers just don't show up because of problems described in the article.  </p>
  
