														<p style="margin:0px 0px 30px;font-size:16px;line-height:23px;font-weight:300;font-family:nyt-franklin, arial, sans-serif;padding:0px;width:auto;color:rgb(34, 34, 34);display:inline-block;">This saddens me beyond belief. Workers being sent home because sales are slow? being called on demand? Who and what are we working for? Not all of our so called mistakes in life are ours alone, there is vast, vast inequality. How can we solve this? Society needs to be restructured to ensure our humanity is principal. What can we do? We need a new progressive era. All of us are competing with each other instead of helping each other and this is a side effect of our economic system. We need social change centered on our human life quality</p>
  
